Proposition.
In the local-balance regime of cumulative cube-root transport,

    M^3 ∝ g_b g_obs,

with

    g_b(r) = G M_b(r) / r^2,
    g_obs(r) = V(r)^2 / r.

At large radius, where V(r) → V_∞, the loading field scales as

    M(r) ∼ (G M_b V_∞^2)^(1/3) r^(-1).

Hence the cumulative stiffness coordinate at the turnover radius obeys

    u(R_s) ∼ (G M_b V_∞^2)^(1/3) Λ_s,

where Λ_s is a weakly varying logarithmic structural factor. If the
turnover threshold corresponds to a common normalized saturation
condition across galaxies, then Λ_s is approximately universal and the
family-level scaling becomes

    V_∞^4 ∝ G M_b.

Thus the baryonic Tully–Fisher relation is the global saturation
condition of the same cumulative transport law that generates the
master curve and the radial acceleration relation.
